o an arbitrary URL after failed authentication. Due to how the OAuth protocol works, the attacker would need to MITM or otherwise tamper with the request from a local network, as the OAuth URL in question was not directly accessible from a link. This means that this vulnerability could only be exploited in a limited set of circumstances. \u003c/p\u003e\n"},{"category":"researcher","can_view?":true,"can_create?":false}]}